:: PAINT2Story {"position":"100,440","size":"160,120"}
 <img id="cecilia-painting" 
         src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YixuanQu/Digital-heritage-and-multimedia/main/img/CONVERSIONE%20DI%20SAN%20PAOLO.jpg" 
         style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto; transform-origin: center 97%; transform: scale(1.0); transition: transform 9.5s cubic-bezier(0.15, 0.85, 0.45, 1);text-align: center;">
 A new voice speaks — deep, and a little ashamed.
“Hello. They call me Paul. I was a hard man once. I hunted people who believed in Christ. I was strong, and I was proud. A painter named Ludovico Carracci painted this exact moment — the moment everything changed for me. I hung in a small chapel inside the great church of San Francesco, here in Bologna. Then they took me down and brought me here.”
He pauses. “Before you judge me — look at me carefully. Something is happening to me. Can you see what?”

[[Look closer.->PAINT2Question]]


