[[Look again.->PAINT6Question]]


:: PAINT6Story {"position":"100,950","size":"160,120"}
<div style="text-align: center; margin: 5px 0;">
    <div style="display: inline-block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid #d4af37; font-size: 0;">
        <img class="strage-cinema-zoom" 
             src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YixuanQu/Digital-heritage-and-multimedia/main/img/STRAGE%20DEGLI%20INNOCENTI.jpg" 
             style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0; transform-origin: center top;">
        <div class="strage-top-glow"></div>
    </div>
</div>
A gentle voice speaks, careful and sad.
“Hello. I am hard to look at, I know. I show a terrible day: a cruel king sent his soldiers to harm the youngest children, and the mothers could do nothing but cry and run. A painter named Guido Reni made me — and he made even this pain beautiful, so the world would never forget it. I hung in the great Basilica di San Domenico, until they brought me here.”
A pause. “Look at me carefully. The painting is dark — but at the very top, there is hope. Can you find it?”

[[Look closer.->PAINT6Question]]


:: PEnd [museum-bg] {"position":"320,1120","size":"160,120"}
“They took us from the city,” the voices say, “and the city forgot. But you walked in. You looked closer. You remembered. Thank you for bringing us home.”
The room is quiet again. But it does not feel empty anymore.

